<br>
We get 3 different mana draining songs in our career to L60.<br>
<br>
1st one is our L35 song, Denon's Dissension. It's an AE so not very useful in lots of places. And not very good, making it totally useless. If you must know, it drains 31 mana per shot, so must be sung continually to be any good. Only good part is, that multiple bards stack here.<br>
<br>
The second one, Cassindra's Insipid Ditty, is a little better, but is L57. It's target based and will drain 15 mana per tick, for 3 ticks, as well as debuff int/wis 15 or 35 with a banjo. This one leaves an icon, so only one bard can sing this.<br>
<br>
Our best manadrain by far is a new L60 song from Luclin, Ervaj's Lost Composition. This one is target based and drain 220 mana or 484 with a horn, and just like the L35 it can be sung by more than bard.<br>
<br>
So what's the stratics here?<br>
Don't bother with the L35 one. L57 is good for one application at least. Since the initial debuff of int and wis drops mana a bit, but after that it's kinda iffy.<br>
The L60 one is actually very good, and you can bet that I will use that on the white wurms in ToV when I get to 60.<br>
Unfortunatly it's a drop in SoL so I have to get my butt up there and get it first.<br>
<br>
<br>
PS. All the numbers quoted is what I would do today at L55 with the instruments I got ATM.<br>
