<br>
Ervaj's Lost Composition:<br>
cast time of 3<br>
recast of 13<br>
220 points manadrain<br>
1.0*220=220 (singing)<br>
1.8*220=396 (Epic)  &lt;--- Me want this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
2.5*220=550 (Immaculate Shell horn) &lt;--- My best horn<br>
Add another 44 point per level of Instrument mastery (AA class skill)<br>
Making it 550 mana every 16 seconds (in my case)<br>
<br>
Level 60 enchanter<br>
3 second cast time<br>
8 seconds recast<br>
370 mana per cast<br>
Making it 370 mana every 11 seconds<br>
<br>
Now for the comparison:<br>
Enchanter: 370/11 = 33.63 mana per second<br>
Me: 550/16 = 34.375 mana per second<br>
Epic+IM3: 528/16 = 33.0 mana per second<br>
<br>
As you can see, I would drain slightly more mana per time than the enchanter, also, keep in mind that he will be spending more time doing so (same cast-time, less recast-time), and that he will spend 150 mana each cast.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if there are any focus items that effect manadrains for enchanters, I don't think so though <br>
<br>
Don't forget chanters can cast Theft of Thought every two minutes which drains 400 mana and gives them 375 mana back, and Wandering Mind every 3 minutes which drains 120 mana and gives them 115 mana back (but only 1 chanter can be casting wandering mind on a mob).<br>
<br>
PS. I Modified the numbers slightly from the original thread to reflect the manadrain I would do if I was L60 today (obviously, since it's a L60 song <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
PPS. Enchanter numbers are direct quote from the mentioned thread, so don't blame me if they're wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
